statements.sql: select column_name as `column_name` from information_schema.columns where table_schema = 'pigeon_app' and table_name = 'roles'

select `roles`.*, `model_has_roles`.`model_id` as `pivot_model_id`, `model_has_roles`.`role_id` as `pivot_role_id`, `model_has_roles`.`model_type` as `pivot_model_type` from `roles` inner join `model_has_roles` on `roles`.`id` = `model_has_roles`.`role_id` where `model_has_roles`.`model_id` = 1 and `model_has_roles`.`model_type` = 'App\Models\User'

select `tournaments`.*, (select count(*) from `tournament_details` where `tournaments`.`id` = `tournament_details`.`tournament_id`) as `details_count` from `tournaments` group by `type` order by `type` asc

SELECT
users.id,
users.name as player,
clubs.name as club,
SUM(tournament_details.points) as players_total_points,
(
SELECT
COUNT(*)
FROM
tournament_details
WHERE
tournament_details.user_id = users.id
GROUP BY
tournament_details.user_id
) as tournaments_joined_count
FROM
users
INNER JOIN
club_users
ON
club_users.user_id = users.id
INNER JOIN
clubs
ON
clubs.id = club_users.club_id
INNER JOIN
tournament_details
ON
tournament_details.user_id = users.id
GROUP BY
users.id
select * from `user_details` where `user_details`.`user_id` = 1 and `user_details`.`user_id` is not null limit 1
